White feathers are interspersed within these patterns, adding to the complexity and visual interest.

The wing shape is relatively broad and rounded, typical of many warbler species. The size of the wing in relation to the bird's body is moderate, neither too large nor too small, which is consistent with the overall proportions of the bird.

Unique features include the bold black and white stripes that run along the wing edges, as well as the yellow patches that stand out prominently against the darker background.
